ProtoDefines:
. "If $D_f$ is unbounded, we say that $$
\lim_{|\mathbf{X}|\to\infty} f(\mathbf{X})=L \quad
\textrm{(finite)}\quad $$ if for every $\epsilon>0$, there is a
number $R$ such that $$ |f(\mathbf{X})-L|<\epsilon \quad
\textrm{whenever}\quad \ |\mathbf{X}|\ge R \quad \textrm{and}\quad
\mathbf{X}\in D_f. $$"
